<h1>Acromine Disambiguation Demonstration</h1>

<h2>Terms of Use</h2>
By using the Acromine Disambiguation service, you agree to the general <a href="http://www.nactem.ac.uk/terms_conditions.php">Terms and Conditions of Use for the NaCTeM Website</a>, in addition to the following Terms of Use for Acromine Disambiguation:
<ul> 
<li>Please let us know that you are using Acromine Disambiguation by <a href="mailto:nactem-services@listserv.manchester.ac.uk">email</a>. </li> 
<li>Please cite the following when publishing work that uses Acromine Disambiguation: <br/>
Okazaki, N., Ananiadou, S., Tsujii, J. (2010) <a href="http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/btq129">Building a High Quality Sense Inventory for Improved Abbreviation Disambiguation</a>. <i>Bioinformatics</i>, (in press), Oxford University Press.</li>
<li>Please credit and link to the NaCTeM website (<a href="http://www.nactem.ac.uk">http://nactem.ac.uk</a>) in any electonic services beased on the Acromine Disambiguation service or resulting data.
</li>
<li>Please <a href="mailto:nactem-services@listserv.manchester.ac.uk">contact us</a> in advance if you plan to use the service for bulk processing. Acromine Disambiguation is a freely available service from the academic domain. This means that it is necessary to limit server load and give preference to individual users. Excessive server load may result in IP addresses or institutions being blocked from using the Acromine Disambiguation service. 
</li>


